## UI flickering (one-shot callbacks)

- **QR scan result flickers (flips between result and scanner)**  
  The scanner library calls the success callback repeatedly while the QR is in view. Each call ran the same handler (e.g. `handleLookup` or set `scannedToken`), which cleared or overwrote state so the UI kept toggling.  
  → Use a **latch**: e.g. `scanHandled`. On first success set `scanHandled = true` and process; in the callback do `if (scanHandled) return` so later calls are ignored. Reset the latch in "start over" flows (Cancel, failed lookup, or when user opens camera again).

- **"Token is already in use" (or any lookup error) keeps flashing**  
  Lookup returned non-success (e.g. token in_use); we set `scanHandled = false` so the next scanner tick ran again → handler cleared `error` then set it again → message flashed.  
  → Treat the error as a **consumed** result: set `scanHandled = true` when showing "already in use" (or similar) so the scanner doesn’t keep re-triggering.   Reset `scanHandled` when the user takes a "try again" action (e.g. clicking Start camera) so the next scan is accepted.

- **Display Board (or any page) flickers after scan then "OK GOT IT" — rapid back/forth**  
  Scanner (html5-qrcode) fires `onScan` many times per second while the QR is in view. Each call did `router.visit(...)`, so we stacked hundreds of navigations.  
  → Use a **latch** in the scan handler: `if (scanHandled) return; scanHandled = true;` then navigate once. Reset `scanHandled = false` when the user opens the scanner again (e.g. "TAP TO SCAN QR CODE" button). Same pattern as Triage.

- **Triage flickers after successful bind — doesn't return to ready state**  
  Scanner fires late callbacks after resetScan() clears state. Setting `scanHandled = false` in resetScan opens the door; a late callback then re-sets `scannedToken` and flips back to confirm view.  
  → In `resetScan()`, set `scanHandled = true` (block late callbacks). Only set `scanHandled = false` when user clicks "Start camera". When stopping camera, set `scanHandled = true`.

